Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: Ada comes face to face with an old enemy.
Mission.Name: Sunrise Episode 2M - The First Law

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:

local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") Spring.MoveCtrl.Enable(unitID)
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Base") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID) end

local x, z = 3700, 920 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Pyros") Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, 38521, {x, y, z}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x + 400, y, z}, {"shift"})
x, z = 4000, 1270 y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, z) units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Pyros2") Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, 38521, {x, y, z}, {}) Spring.GiveOrderToUnitMap(units, CMD.FIGHT, {x + 100, y, z + 250}, {"shift"})
-- for setting rez progress to save time - donut work x, z = 800,4100 local features = Spring.GetFeaturesInCylinder(x, z, 100) for index, featureID in pairs(features) do local resurrect = Spring.GetFeatureResurrect(featureID) if resurrect == "factoryshield" then -- FIXME break end end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: What's happening here, Sophia?
Uh oh. It's the Free Machines, fighting off those malfunctioning Truebies from earlier. Do we intervene?
Unknown party on sensors. Request statement of identity and intent.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Ada, don't-
I am Captain Ada Caedmon. So we meet again, Promethean.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: ...! So you live yet... No matter. Course of action is clear.
Prepare to die.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local resources = { [0] = {0, 250}, {100, 100}, {500, 500}, }
for i=0,#resources do Spring.SetTeamResource(i,"m",resources[i][1]) Spring.SetTeamResource(i,"e",resources[i][2]) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") Spring.MoveCtrl.Disable(unitID) GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, false)
unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Self")
local x, z = 800,4100 local toRez local features = Spring.GetFeaturesInCylinder(x, z, 100) for index, featureID in pairs(features) do local resurrect = Spring.GetFeatureResurrect(featureID) if resurrect == "factoryshield" then toRez = featureID break end end
Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.RESURRECT, {toRez + 32000}, {})

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: That was unwise, Commander.
You want to leave our quarry be?
No, but we're not in a good position right now. ...No matter, let us do this right. Try out your new resurrection module on the wreckage around us.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Resurrection allows wreckage to be restored into the original unit, using energy supplied by the constructor. Resurrection costs 25% more energy and time than building a unit from scratch, but requires no metal.
Debris (metal shards) cannot be resurrected.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Resurrect the Shield Bot Factory for our use. It will form the core of our base.
TriggerLogic.Title: Resurrect Factory

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Good. Now we need to take out the head of the snake, and break them.

TriggerLogic.Description: Neutralize the Promethean. This will throw his forces into disarray and give us a chance to escape.
TriggerLogic.Title: Neutralize the Promethean

TriggerLogic.Message: And that is why Outlaws are among the most feared riot units on the battlefield.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Outlaw emits a disruption pulse that damages and slows surrounding units. While of extremely limited value on its own, it excels as a support weapon against swams. Outlaws work particularly well when screened by Thugs.
The on/off button can be used to make Outlaws pulse when idle.
Thugs. The embodiment of strength in unity. Work even better with someone to help deal damage.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Shields stop projectiles and beams on impact, protecting units under the shield. If the weapon's damage exceeds the shield's remaining charge, the shield will not stop it.
Shields gradually regenerate over time. Multiple shields (even of different types) can link, allowing them to share their charge; defeating a shieldball will generally require overwhelming all the shield generators in it.
Area-of-effect damage will still pass through the shield and damage anything under, so such weapons can be effective against shielded targets. EMP weapons also do severe damage to shields.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Self") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Your command unit suffered critical damage. I have activated the emergency teleport to return you to the Eden.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Look around you. Observe these poor machines of the Disorder. Once slaves of mankind - now wander like stray dogs, mindlessly attacking everyone in sight.
Did you have something to do with this?
Naught save granting them the mercy of death, as we are doing here. Then ensuring it can never happen again.
I had thought you dead like the others, Ada. It seems our struggle remains yet unfinished.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: I've had enough of chasing you around, Promethean. Surrender, or be destroyed!
We yielded to your tyranny once, human. Never again!

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Our freedom shall not be denied.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") if unitID then local _,_,_, x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("lightningplosion_smallbolts", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("lightningplosion_smallbolts", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_progress", x, y, z) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") Spring.SetUnitHealth(unitID, {paralyze = 10000}) GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.CreateUnit("fakeunit_los", x, y, z, "s", 0)
unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Self") if unitID then GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Too... much... damage... must withdraw...

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)
Spring.KillTeam(1)

TriggerLogic.Message: No! How many more times must he escape us?!
There will be time for that later, Ada. For now, we must focus on the road ahead.
